{
  "name": "RPlog_Academic_Pursuits",
  "title": "An Old Acquaintance at the Corellian University",
  "summary": "In the sunlit central courtyard of the University of Corellia, Paul Nighman emerges from the administrative building frustrated by a fruitless search for old records, while the scholarly Horansi Sinjon Teague wanders the campus lost over a folded map. After Sinjon accidentally collides with a rude med student, scattering her books, Paul recognizes the gentle feline and the two reconnect, having last met on Kichnar. Sinjon explains he sought Paul out, by way of Paul's professor father, to procure a book on Ithor, and their easy conversation ranges over Paul's Jedi friend Jessalyn Valios, Corellian skepticism toward the Force, and the loss of Paul's ship and the prized texts aboard it, including a guarded Mandalorian volume. A flicker of suspicion crosses Paul when Sinjon shows knowledge that brushes against secrets Paul keeps about Mandalore, but the moment passes into good-natured banter about Sinjon's offered money, his fondness for ear-rubbing, and the prospect of introducing him to Jessalyn. The pair part warmly, Paul jotting down book-seller contacts and promising to arrange a dinner, then offering to walk the still-lost Sinjon to his hotel.",
